summary.name: Antibiotic_Effectiveness
summary.dataset_description: This dataset contains information about the effectiveness of different antibiotics on various bacteria.

properties.description: Minimum inhibitory concentration (MIC) of Penicillin in micrograms per milliliter
Minimum inhibitory concentration (MIC) of Streptomycin in micrograms per milliliter
Minimum inhibitory concentration (MIC) of Neomycin in micrograms per milliliter
Gram staining result of the bacteria (positive or negative)

goals.question: What is the distribution of Penicillin MIC values?
goals.rationale: This helps to understand the range of Penicillin MIC values and the frequency of their occurrence.

goals.question: How does the distribution of Streptomycin MIC values compare to that of Penicillin?
goals.visualization: box plot of Streptomycin and Penicillin
goals.rationale: This helps to compare the central tendency, spread and outliers of Streptomycin and Penicillin MIC values.

goals.question: What is the relationship between Neomycin MIC values and Gram staining result?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of Neomycin and Gram_Staining
goals.rationale: This helps to understand if there is any correlation between Neomycin MIC values and Gram staining result.

goals.question: Which bacteria species have the highest and lowest MIC values for each antibiotic?
goals.visualization: bar chart of maximum and minimum MIC values for each antibiotic by Bacteria
goals.rationale: This helps to identify the bacteria species that are most and least susceptible to each antibiotic.

goals.question: How does the MIC value distribution vary across different genera of bacteria?
goals.visualization: violin plot of MIC values by Genus
goals.rationale: This helps to understand if there are any significant differences in MIC value distribution across different genera of bacteria.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.hist(data['Penicillin'])
    plt.xlabel('Penicillin MIC values')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    plt.title('What is the distribution of Penicillin MIC values?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data.boxplot(column=['Streptomycin', 'Penicillin'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=45 if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20 else 0)
    plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title("How does the distribution of Streptomycin MIC values compare to that of Penicillin?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    
    antibiotics = ['Penicillin', 'Streptomycin', 'Neomycin']
    min_max_values = []
    
    for antibiotic in antibiotics:
        min_value = data.loc[data[antibiotic].idxmin()]['Bacteria']
        max_value = data.loc[data[antibiotic].idxmax()]['Bacteria']
        min_max_values.append((min_value, max_value))
    
    min_max_df = pd.DataFrame(min_max_values, columns=['Min MIC', 'Max MIC'], index=antibiotics)
    min_max_df.plot(kind='bar', rot=0)
    
    plt.title("Which bacteria species have the highest and lowest MIC values for each antibiotic?")
    plt.xlabel("Antibiotics")
    plt.ylabel("Bacteria")
    
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.violinplot(x='Genus', y='MIC', data=data)
    plt.title("How does the MIC value distribution vary across different genera of bacteria?", wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
